    <item> 
     <title>Last-Minute Hallmark Award Tips</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/last-minute-hallmark-tips 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2015-01-14T00:00:00-06:00"&gt;Wednesday, January 14, 2015&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&amp;rsquo;re in the final weeks of &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/benefits/awards/hallmark"&gt;Hallmark Award&lt;/a&gt; submissions. As you prepare your entries for Honors in Action Project and College Project awards, use these judging rubrics as a guide and checklist.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Honors in Action Project and College Project award entries are due to Phi Theta Kappa Headquarters by 5 pm CST on Wednesday, January 28. For both entries, write in a way that walks judges through the process of developing your projects as they read your entry. When you have completed your first drafts, edit, edit, edit! Check and double-check spelling and grammar for the best presentation possible.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Want to hear more advice directly from Phi Theta Kappa&amp;#39;s Deans? Check out these short &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLLP2bJxRD5IY2P0vDGVX5LhXGJAI3WRYh"&gt;Honors in Action videos.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exemplary Honors in Action project should include the following elements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Academic Rigor of Research: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Use at least eight wide-ranging academic publications and/or expert sources that include different points of view on the chapter&amp;rsquo;s selected theme of the Honors Study Topic. &amp;bull; Develop critical thinking skills for project participants. &amp;bull; Choose research that provides substantial material to consider when determining a project to implement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resourcefulness: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Ambition and perseverance in pursuit of the required substantial research and inspired resourcefulness to implement the project effectively.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Exercise of Leadership and Leadership Development: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Substantive opportunities for chapter members to exercise and advance leadership skills. &amp;bull; Effective planning and teamwork. &amp;bull; Effective, intentional and thoughtful educational and training activities and opportunities that improved the exercise of leadership.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Persistence: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Demonstration of a strong commitment to overcome obstacles or challenges. &amp;bull; Response to challenges with flexibility and creativity to keep the project on track.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Action/Service/Advocacy: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Clear project objectives that emphasized the importance of taking action or serving. &amp;bull; Heightened awareness of self and community in relation to global issues on the part of project participants. &amp;bull; Increased appreciation for the value of informed action and service as a lifelong endeavor. &amp;bull; Action clearly developed from research conclusions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cooperative Effort/Outreach: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Collaboration with a wide variety of audiences, including ALL of the following: the college, community and others in OR beyond the region. &amp;bull; Effective and efficient communication among the participating individuals and/or organizations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Contribution of the project to the improvement of an issue with significant short-term impact and potential for long-term impact. &amp;bull; Exceptional quantitative and qualitative outcomes. &amp;bull; Assessment by the chapter about what they learned and how they grew as scholars and servant leaders. &amp;bull; Identification of what opportunities remain to have a further impact on the issue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/benefits/awards/hallmark/hia-excerpts"&gt;Read excerpts from award-winning Honors in Action Project entries.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Winning College Project entries should meet the following criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preparation: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; The chapter met with appropriate administrators and participated fully by being active listeners and brainstorming ideas. &amp;bull; Everyone gave careful consideration to what type of project would be most beneficial to the college to help fulfill its mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership Development: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; There was exceptional planning and teamwork. &amp;bull; Members used this opportunity to exercise and advance their leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cooperative Effort/Communications: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Chapter members demonstrated a strong commitment to working with college administrators before, during and after the project. &amp;bull; Members responded to any challenges with flexibility and creativity to keep the project on track.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; The project&amp;rsquo;s outcomes were exceptional and included both quantitative and qualitative elements. &amp;bull; The chapter assessed what they learned and how they grew as scholars and servant leaders. &amp;bull; The chapter identified what opportunities remain to either improve the project or to enhance the relationship with the college administration.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/benefits/awards/hallmark/college-project-excerpts"&gt;Read excerpts from outstanding College Project entries.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
