    <item> 
     <title>How to Create Your CollegeFish.org Profile</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/how-to-create-a-collegefish-profile 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-10-09T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Thursday, October 9, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the second &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/news/collegefish-completion-transfer-month"&gt;Community College Completion and Transfer Month&lt;/a&gt; gets underway, we&amp;rsquo;re going to start with the basics: setting up your &lt;a href="http://collegefish.org/"&gt;CollegeFish.org&lt;/a&gt; profile.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="caption_photo right"&gt;&lt;a class="colorbox colorbox-insert-image" href="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/Get-Hooked-Logo.jpg" rel="gallery-all" title=""&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/Get-Hooked-Logo.jpg?itok=16ZDydf6" title="" typeof="foaf:Image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Share your Community College Completion &amp;amp; Transfer Month events on the &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/collegefish"&gt;CollegeFish.org Facebook page.&lt;/a&gt; #hookedoncompletion #fishfanatics&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;This is where it all begins,&amp;rdquo; said Jennifer Blalock, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Chief Student Support Officer who oversees CollegeFish.org. &amp;ldquo;Creating a CollegeFish.org account will help you search, select, secure and succeed in completing your associate degree or two-year college certificate, transferring to the four-year college of your choice and competing for scholarships.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Need an extra incentive to create your profile? All throughout October, when you create a CollegeFish.org profile, you&amp;rsquo;ll be eligible to &lt;strong&gt;win a $1,000 scholarship!&lt;/strong&gt; One lucky winner will be announced in early November. You can also get qualified by logging into your &lt;a href="http://collegefish.org/"&gt;CollegeFish.org account&lt;/a&gt; anytime in October; by liking the &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/collegefish"&gt;CollegeFish.org Facebook page&lt;/a&gt; and posting your name, college and email address; and by attending a webinar and providing your name, college and email.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do all of these activities and attend multiple webinars to increase your chances of winning. &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/news/collegefish-completion-transfer-month"&gt;Find a full schedule of webinars.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Setting up your CollegeFish.org profile is free and easy. There are several steps, but each one brings you closer to more than $37 million in transfer scholarships that are available &amp;mdash; many exclusively to Phi Theta Kappa members.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Go to &lt;a href="http://www.collegefish.org/"&gt;CollegeFish.org&lt;/a&gt; and click on &amp;ldquo;Log in&amp;rdquo; in the upper right-hand corner of the page. The next page is a login page similar to Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s sign-in page at ptk.org. If you have never logged in to CollegeFish.org, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to click &amp;ldquo;Create Account&amp;rdquo; next to the green Login button. One thing to note: if you&amp;#39;re a Phi Theta Kappa member, your CollegeFish.org login credentials should be the same as your credentials for ptk.org.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Next, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to fill in your name and email address and choose a password. Entering your birth date is optional. Important: your password must be at least eight characters and include only numbers and letters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will then receive an email with a validation code from donotreply@ptk.org. If it&amp;rsquo;s not in your inbox, be sure to check your junk or trash folders. Open the email and click on the hyperlink, and you&amp;rsquo;ll be taken directly to the next step. As a Phi Theta Kappa member, you&amp;rsquo;ll probably want to connect your CollegeFish.org and ptk.org accounts by choosing &amp;ldquo;Link Phi Theta Kappa member id.&amp;rdquo; If you&amp;rsquo;re not a Phi Theta Kappa member &amp;mdash; CollegeFish.org is open to all two-year college students &amp;mdash; simply choose &amp;ldquo;Done.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The next step is to verify your access. There are three options:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;I am a Phi Theta Kappa member and a student at a 2-year school.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;I am a student at a two-year school.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;I am not a student at a two-year school.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Select the category that fits, then click on the green arrow in the lower right-hand corner to navigate through the questions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once you&amp;rsquo;ve validated your name and input your community college and date of birth, a welcome screen will appear. Click on &amp;ldquo;Let&amp;rsquo;s get started&amp;rdquo; to complete your personalized profile and receive both college and scholarship matches.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll then go through a series of questions &amp;mdash; each one will help CollegeFish.org find the best-fit options for your future. Once you have answered all of the questions and completed the profile, you&amp;rsquo;ll receive both scholarship recommendations and college matches. Then, simply click on them to learn more and start your search!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now, you can save your top-choice scholarships and colleges in your moneybag and fishbowl, respectively. You can add important dates to your calendar, create goals, monitor your progress through your personalized plan and much more. To learn more about everything CollegeFish.org has to offer, make plans to attend one of these informative webinars:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Oct. 14, 1 &amp;amp; 7 pm CST, CollegeFish.org Search &amp;amp; Select 101&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Oct. 15, 1 &amp;amp; 7 pm CST, CollegeFish.org Scholarship Resume &amp;amp; Essay 101&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Oct. 21, 1 &amp;amp; 7 pm CST, Creating a Successful CollegeFish.org Campus-Wide Rollout, hosted by the Alpha Phi Kappa Chapter at Bluegrass Community and Technical College&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Oct. 22, 1 &amp;amp; 7 pm CST, FishFinance: College Savings 101, hosted by the Omicron Beta Chapter at Mesa Community College&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
