    <item> 
     <title>Best Practices: Make Your Fall Scholarship Application Stand Out</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/fall-scholarship-app-tips 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-10-06T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Monday, October 6, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hundreds of Phi Theta Kappa members apply for scholarships using the &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/become-a-member/scholarships"&gt;Fall Scholarship Application&lt;/a&gt; each year. So how do you make sure your application stands out from the rest?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Christin Grissom, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Director of Scholarship Operations, shares these tips that will help your scholarship application be one the judges will remember.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply EARLY! &amp;bull; Give yourself time to create an exceptional scholarship entry. &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; Don&amp;rsquo;t wait until the last minute to apply. Deadlines can make or break you. &amp;bull; Transcripts and Student Assessments take time to obtain. &amp;bull; Online applications can&amp;rsquo;t be completed two hours ahead of the deadline; give yourself time in case you run into technological or login problems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create a scholarship RESUME before beginning the application. &lt;/strong&gt;Outlining engagement and hours of service in the following areas can help prevent important omissions. As you build experience in these areas, update your scholarship resume to quickly access necessary information to complete future scholarship applications. Your resume should include:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Education&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Campus Involvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Community Service&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Scholarships and Awards&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work Experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read the PURPOSE of the Scholarship. &lt;/strong&gt;Understanding the purpose of the scholarship helps you to both customize and strengthen your scholarship entry.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish solid STUDENT ASSESSMENTS.&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;bull; Choose a recommender who knows you well and can elaborate on specific and pertinent information outlined within in your application. &amp;bull; Explain the criteria of the award &amp;mdash; send a copy of your application to them. &amp;bull; Give recommenders ample time to complete the Student Assessment. &amp;bull; Send thank-you letters afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When writing your ESSAY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stick to the topic.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use vivid details, share numbers or facts and address the impact of your engagement to make your application stand out.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;PROOFREAD, PROOFREAD, PROOFREAD! Have others proofread your essay to provide feedback and use this to revise your entry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your application should be NEAT and FLAWLESS.&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;bull; It can be difficult to identify misspellings, grammatical or punctuation mistakes when completing online applications. Compose responses in a separate document to help you identify errors before transferring them to your application. &amp;bull; Never submit your first draft. &amp;bull; Organize information with bullets. &amp;bull; This is your one chance in front of the judges &amp;mdash; make a good impression!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have MULTIPLE people CRITIQUE your application. &lt;/strong&gt;Ensuring your application is cohesive and flawless from start to finish strengthens your entry.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double-check your application for COMPLETION. &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;An incomplete application is as good as NO application. All components of the application, including transcripts and Student Assessments, must be submitted by the deadline for your application to be considered complete.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRINT your application before submission. &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; You can use it as a reference for future scholarship entries. &amp;bull; If it gets lost, you&amp;rsquo;ll have a spare.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Above all, do not miss the deadline! Applications are due December 1, 2014!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Read more about the scholarships offered on the &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/become-a-member/scholarships"&gt;Fall Scholarship Application.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
     <pubdate>
      Mon, 06 Oct 2014 15:05:28 +0000
     </pubdate> 
     <dc:creator>
      cogsweep
     </dc:creator> 
     <guid ispermalink="false">
      241017 at https://www.ptk.org
     </guid> 
