    <item> 
     <title>Fall Scholarship Application Features Some Changes, Opens Oct. 1</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/fall-scholarship-app-changes 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-10-01T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Wednesday, October 1, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/become-a-member/scholarships"&gt;Fall Scholarship Application&lt;/a&gt; opens October 1, and brings with it access to approximately $520,000 for students preparing to complete a certificate or associate degree or planning to transfer to a four-year college or university.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some significant changes have been made to the application in an effort to both streamline the application process and to make the application itself more user-friendly. These changes affect students, college nominators and those asked to submit student assessments (formerly letters of recommendation). The application deadline is December 1.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;With nearly $1 million up for grabs through our fall and spring scholarship applications, we want to ensure that as many eligible students apply as possible,&amp;rdquo; said Christin Grissom, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Director of Scholarship Operations. &amp;ldquo;The ease and convenience of our scholarship application is one of the largest determinants of the number of students that will apply.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We&amp;rsquo;ve heard the feedback, and we&amp;rsquo;ve made the changes that will hopefully encourage even more students to apply for these incredible scholarship awards.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, students will now self-identify with a college to access the application. In the past, students had to receive a special code from the college&amp;rsquo;s designated scholarship nominator.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Students will also notice fewer uploads during the application process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Uploads have been tremendous barriers to students completing our application,&amp;rdquo; Grissom said. &amp;ldquo;We&amp;rsquo;ve cut down on front-end uploads and will be requiring minimal uploads on the back end before we select winners.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In lieu of letters of recommendation, recommenders will be asked to complete a student assessment &amp;mdash; a questionnaire assessment within the application. This change will both increase the quality of responses and reduce upload barriers for recommenders as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We hope these changes will benefit the application process for students, advisors and nominators alike,&amp;rdquo; Grissom said. &amp;ldquo;Our two-year college students are among the hardest working students out there, and they deserve as much financial help as they can get to encourage them to continue their education.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The following scholarships are administered on the &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/become-a-member/scholarships"&gt;Fall Scholarship Application:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hites Transfer Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be a Phi Theta Kappa member&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;10 scholarships of $7,500 each, for a total of $75,000 awarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Guistwhite Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be a Phi Theta Kappa member&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;15 scholarships of $5,000 each, for a total of $75,000 awarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;GEICO Pathway to Completion Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s Degree Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be a Phi Theta Kappa member&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must apply for the Guistwhite Scholarship&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2 scholarships of $1,500 each, for a total of $3,000 awarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;All-USA Community College Academic Team Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open to non-members; must be nominated by your college&amp;rsquo;s designated nominator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;20 scholarships of $2,500 each, for a total of $50,000 awarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Coca-Cola Community College Academic Team Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open to non-members; must be nominated by your college&amp;rsquo;s designated nominator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;50 Gold Scholar Awards of $1,500; 50 Silver Scholar Awards of $1,250; and 50 Bronze Scholar Awards of $1,000, for a total of $187,500 awarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Coca-Cola New Century Scholars Scholarship&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open to non-members; must be nominated by your college&amp;rsquo;s designated nominator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Awarded to the top-scoring student from each of the 50 United States, Canada or other sovereign nation where at least one Phi Theta Kappa chapter resides&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;52 scholarships of $2,000, for a total of $104,000&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;All-State Community College Academic Team&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be nominated by your college&amp;rsquo;s designated nominator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must reside in one of the 38 participating states&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;More than $41 million available&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
