    <item> 
     <title>Members to be Published in Nota Bene, Receive $3,000 in Scholarships</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/nota-bene-2014-winners 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-09-22T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Monday, September 22, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Literary works from 26 Phi Theta Kappa members have been chosen from more than 960 entries for publication in the 2014 edition of &lt;em&gt;Nota Bene&lt;/em&gt;, the Society&amp;#39;s honors anthology. Authors of the five most outstanding entries received $3,000 in &lt;em&gt;Nota Bene&lt;/em&gt; scholarships.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Patrick Hughes from Mountain View Community College in Dallas, Texas, received the Nell Ewing Citation Award for best entry in Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s annual &lt;em&gt;Nota Bene &lt;/em&gt;literary competition for his short story, &amp;ldquo;The Reluctant Warrior.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp; He expressed his gratitude for the honor and said he planned to use the $1,000 scholarship to further his education and seek more advanced degrees.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;ldquo;I&amp;rsquo;ve been writing ever since I was in high school, generally science fiction and fantasy,&amp;rdquo; said Hughes, a biology major. &amp;ldquo;I would like to study the effects of space on living creatures, but I would still like to continue to write on the side and hopefully get published.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nota Bene&lt;/em&gt; was founded in 1994 to showcase exceptional writing among community college students. Copies of &lt;em&gt;Nota Bene&lt;/em&gt; are distributed to all community college libraries and to Phi Theta Kappa leaders. Since the establishment of the journal and the scholarship program, $60,000 in scholarships have been presented to Phi Theta Kappa members, and more than 300 students have had their work published. Entries for the &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/nota-bene"&gt;2015 &lt;em&gt;Nota Bene&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; competition are due April 3, 2015.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Winners of the 2014 Nota Bene scholarships are&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;u&gt;Ewing Citation Scholarship of $1,000, for the Best Overall Entry:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Reluctant Warrior&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Short Story&lt;br /&gt;Patrick Hughes&lt;br /&gt;Mountain View Community College, Dallas, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;u&gt;Reynolds Awards of $500 each:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Mama&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Short Story&lt;br /&gt;Cassandra Van Gelder&lt;br /&gt;College of Southern Nevada, Nevada&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Hail Mary&amp;quot; - Short Story&lt;br /&gt;Kaitlyn Worman&lt;br /&gt;Lane Community College, Oregon&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Price Of&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Poem&lt;br /&gt;Daryl Watkins&lt;br /&gt;College of Southern Nevada, Nevada&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Sore Thumb&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Poem&lt;br /&gt;Diana Sherrard&lt;br /&gt;Mt. San Antonio College, California&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;The following students had their work selected for publication:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Research Papers&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;From Wallpapers to Institutes: The 19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; Century&amp;rsquo;s Response to Mental Illness&lt;br /&gt;Stephanie Rodriguez&lt;br /&gt;Lake Sumter State College, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;A Contrast of Mr. Darcy&amp;rsquo;s Motives and Mill&amp;rsquo;s Ideals in Jane Austen&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;Pride and Prejudice&lt;/em&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Caroline France&lt;br /&gt;Greenville Technical College, South Carolina&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Online Education Quandary: Is Higher Education Ready to Embrace the Digital Revolution?&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Lisa Haygood&lt;br /&gt;Fullerton College, California&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;John Adams and the Alien and Sedition Acts&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Nancy Mantick&lt;br /&gt;Ivy Tech Community College, Indiana&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Essays&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Power of Darkness&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Hannah Pruitt&lt;br /&gt;Jones County Junior College, Mississippi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;A Life Outside the Box&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Ashley Rogers&lt;br /&gt;Daytona State College, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Equine-Assisted Therapy: Equine Talent or Magical Properties&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Stacy McElvaney&lt;br /&gt;Red Rocks Community College, Colorado&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Blooms of Integrity&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Elise Jackson&lt;br /&gt;College of DuPage, Illinois&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Short Stories&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Avigail Gemma Reznikoff&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Kandace Kelly&lt;br /&gt;Central Arizona College, Arizona&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Lightning Bug&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Cassandra Van Gelder&lt;br /&gt;College of Southern Nevada, Nevada&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;What Lies Over the Ocean&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Mackenzie Adix&lt;br /&gt;Tacoma Community College, Washington&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Will the Last One Out Please Shut the Door&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Tammara Leminen&lt;br /&gt;Berkshire Community College, Massachusetts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Regret&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Oriana Wood&lt;br /&gt;St. Louis Community College &amp;ndash; Wildwood, Missouri&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Song of the Morning Star&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Lindsay Base&lt;br /&gt;Coffeyville Community College, Kansas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Desperate Decision&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Viviana Mendoza&lt;br /&gt;Lone Star College &amp;ndash; Kingwood, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Poetry&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Listening to Diana Krall on the Radio&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Tammara Leminen&lt;br /&gt;Berkshire Community College, Massachusetts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;One More Push&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Catherine Mahony&lt;br /&gt;Reading Area Community College, Pennsylvania&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Fault Lines&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Zachary Jones&lt;br /&gt;Jackson College, Michigan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;On the Corner of Never and Again&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Zachary Jones&lt;br /&gt;Jackson College, Michigan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Over&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Jocelyn Wagner&lt;br /&gt;Merced College, California&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Lunacy&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Justin Jones&lt;br /&gt;Georgia Highlands College, Georgia&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Just Out of Reach&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Joanne Rosier&lt;br /&gt;Berkshire Community College, Massachusetts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Awaiting the Geese&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Joanne Rosier&lt;br /&gt;Berkshire Community College, Massachusetts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;If Only I Could Think of Sweeter Things to Say&amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Daryl Watkins&lt;br /&gt;College of Southern Nevada, Nevada&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Pandering&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Kathleen Settels-Blackthorne&lt;br /&gt;Irvine Valley College, California&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Hotel Room&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Renee Soasey&lt;br /&gt;Clark Community College, Washington&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Released&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;Nancy Mantick&lt;br /&gt;Ivy Tech Community College, Indiana&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Phi Theta Kappa Honor Society, headquartered in Jackson, Mississippi, is the largest honor society in higher education with 1,285 chapters on college campuses in all 50 of the United States, plus Canada, Germany, the Republic of Palau, Peru, the Republic of the Marshall Islands, the Federated States of Micronesia, the British Virgin Islands, the United Arab Emirates and U.S. territorial possessions. Nearly 3 million students have been inducted since its founding in 1918, with approximately 131,000 students inducted annually.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-item odd"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/191" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Events &amp;amp; Awards&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
