    <item> 
     <title>CollegeFish.org Presents 2014 Transfer Triumph Awards</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/transfer-triumph-awards-given 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-06-06T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Friday, June 6, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.collegefish.org"&gt;CollegeFish.org&lt;/a&gt; recognized 17 college transfer champions during NerdNation 2014, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s annual convention, held in Orlando, Florida. Award winners included two-year college students, faculty and staff members; two-year colleges and transfer officials from four-year colleges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="caption_photo right"&gt;&lt;a class="colorbox colorbox-insert-image" href="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/cf_DSC_1178.jpg" rel="gallery-all" title=""&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/cf_DSC_1178.jpg?itok=HCX--TkJ" title="" typeof="foaf:Image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;Phi Theta Kappa members from Bishop State Community College in Alabama attend the CollegeFish.org Transfer Triumph Awards during NerdNation 2014.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;CollegeFish.org is Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s online college transfer tool, connecting two-year college students with four-year colleges and universities for the completion of a baccalaureate degree.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nearly 800 four-year colleges are represented on CollegeFish.org and offer more than $37 million in transfer scholarships to Phi Theta Kappa members. CollegeFish.org itself is open to all two-year college students at participating community colleges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Since its founding in 2011, CollegeFish has gained many valuable partners and transfer champions at both the two-year and the four-year college levels,&amp;rdquo; said Jennifer Blalock, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Chief Student Support Officer who oversees CollegeFish.org. &amp;ldquo;This is our way of recognizing and celebrating those championing college transfer and completion, who are establishing a standard of best practices for colleges everywhere in transfer success. We look forward to making this an annual part of NerdNation.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The CollegeFish.org Transfer Triumph Awards showcased the best and brightest in two- and four-year college transfer initiatives, programming and pathways. It recognized outstanding innovation at both two-year and four-year college institutions; celebrated collaboration and creativity; and showed appreciation for student advocacy and ambassadorship.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recipients of the 2014 Transfer Triumph Awards are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community College Transfer Trendsetter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Robin Graff, Westchester Community College, New York&lt;br /&gt;Victoria Perry, Bishop State Community College, Alabama&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community College Transfer Champion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bluegrass Community &amp;amp; Technical College, Kentucky&lt;br /&gt;Calhoun Community College, Alabama&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community College Faculty &amp;amp; Staff Fish Fanatic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Heather Owen, Lurleen B. Wallace Community College, Alabama&lt;br /&gt;Cindy Baker, Bluegrass Community &amp;amp; Technical College, Kentucky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community College Student Fish Fanatic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Howard Stephen Guy, Pikes Peak Community College, Colorado&lt;br /&gt;Susann Harding, Tarrant County College, Texas&lt;br /&gt;Christina Urbina, Polk State College, Florida&lt;br /&gt;FeiFei Zeng, Carl Albert State College, Oklahoma&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional Programs &amp;amp; Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jeffrey Rhoads, Arizona State University, Arizona&lt;br /&gt;Neal Richardson, University of Wisconsin-Madison, Wisconsin&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transfer Pathway Innovations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nate Elliott, Rockhurst University, Missouri&lt;br /&gt;Ryan Wagoner, University of Kentucky, Kentucky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partners in Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kevin Caffey, Dallas Baptist University, Texas&lt;br /&gt;Lynn Russell, Mississippi State University, Mississippi&lt;br /&gt;Evangelyn Diaz, University of Pennsylvania-LPS, Pennsylvania&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/191" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Events &amp;amp; Awards&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
