    <item> 
     <title>Meet the 2014-2015 International Officer Candidates</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/meet-the-2014-IO-candidates 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-04-08T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Tuesday, April 8, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to introduce the candidates for the 2014-2015 International Officer positions! Serving as an International Officer is the highest position of student leadership in Phi Theta Kappa. This year, 27 members will be campaigning for your votes at &lt;a href="http://nerdnation.ptk.org"&gt;NerdNation 2014.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Serving as a Phi Theta Kappa International Officer is an incredible opportunity,&amp;rdquo; said Dawneen Banks, the Society&amp;rsquo;s Associate Director of Regional and Chapter Development for Division IV and a former International Vice President. &amp;ldquo;The requirements are many and can be difficult, but the rewards are immeasurable.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can learn more about each candidate by watching the &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/candidatecaucus"&gt;Candidate Caucus,&lt;/a&gt; during which Phi Theta Kappa Executive Director and CEO Dr. Rod Risley interviews each candidate. Full candidate profiles and essays on the Honors Study Topic, &lt;em&gt;Frontiers and the Spirit of Exploration,&lt;/em&gt; are also now available on the &lt;a href="http://nerdnation.ptk.org/experience/elections"&gt;NerdNation website.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Each chapter attending NerdNation in Orlando, Florida, has a designated voting delegate, who for the first time will cast their chapters&amp;rsquo; votes online for International Officer positions. The person designated as the chapter&amp;rsquo;s voting delegate will cast votes in both the Primary and Final Elections.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Political Rallies for the International Officer candidates will be held Thursday, April 24 from 4-5 p.m. and from 9-11 p.m. in the NerdNation Marketplace. Primary polling opens Thursday, April 24, at 10 p.m. and closes Friday, April 25, at 8 a.m.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Candidate Finalists will be announced during the Second General Session Friday, April 25, at 10 a.m., and their speeches will be made in that same session. Conversations with Candidate Finalists will be held April 25 from noon to 1 p.m. in Marketplace. Final polling is open from 11:30 a.m. until 10 p.m. on Friday, April 25.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 2014-2015 International Officers will be announced during the Hallmark Awards Gala on Saturday, April 26, at 4:30 p.m.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Voting delegates will receive an email link to the online voting system once the polls open. Delegates without email access on a personal mobile device may use iPad stations at the Voter Registration Booth near NerdNation Registration to access this email and cast their votes. Be sure to watch the new &lt;a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TtaEKYkBcuk"&gt;video for Voting Delegates&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 2014-2015 International Officer Candidates are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International President&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;James Browne&lt;br /&gt;Kappa Tau Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Metropolitan Community College-Longview&lt;br /&gt;Lee&amp;rsquo;s Summit, Missouri&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ebonee Carpenter&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Lambda Alpha Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Hillsborough Community College&lt;br /&gt;Tampa, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mark Davis II&lt;br /&gt;Mu Tau Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Lansing Community College&lt;br /&gt;Lansing, Michigan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;David A. DeClerck&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Omicron Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Tyler Junior College&lt;br /&gt;Tyler, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jarrett Fletcher&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Gamma Omega Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Valencia College&lt;br /&gt;Orlando, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Eric Trey Mueller&lt;br /&gt;Eta Gamma Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Coffeyville Community College&lt;br /&gt;Coffeyville, Kansas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kevin O&amp;#39;Brien&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Pi Pi Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Community College of Aurora&lt;br /&gt;Aurora, Colorado&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nathaniel Peoples&lt;br /&gt;Beta Sigma Mu Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Tarrant County College&lt;br /&gt;Fort Worth, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Paul Reeck&lt;br /&gt;Beta Nu Chi Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Western Technical College&lt;br /&gt;La Crosse, Wisconsin&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cody J. Young&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Upsilon Sigma Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Jefferson Community &amp;amp; Technical College&lt;br /&gt;Louisville, Kentucky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division I Vice President&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stella Galyean&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Upsilon Eta Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Asheville-Buncombe Technical Community&lt;br /&gt;Asheville, North Carolina&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Megan A. Giles&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Nu Omega Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Harrisburg Area Community College&lt;br /&gt;Harrisburg, Pennsylvania&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Megan Sims&lt;br /&gt;Upsilon Upsilon Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Southwest Virginia Community College&lt;br /&gt;Cedar Bluff, Virginia&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division II Vice President&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rachel M. Carpenter&lt;br /&gt;Upsilon Delta Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Southwest Tennessee Community College&lt;br /&gt;Memphis, Tennessee&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Michael Nguyen&lt;br /&gt;Alpha Lambda Sigma Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Holmes Community College&lt;br /&gt;Ridgeland, Mississippi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jennifer Seymour&lt;br /&gt;Omicron Alpha Chapter&lt;br /&gt;Mississippi Gulf Coast Community College-Jefferson Davis Campus&lt;br /&gt;Gulfport, Mississippi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jesus Manuel Tovar&lt;br /&gt;Omega Gamma Chapter&lt;br /&gt;El Paso Community College&lt;br /&gt;El Paso, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&