    <item> 
     <title>Thirty Named Phi Theta Kappa Distinguished Chapter Officer Teams</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/Thirty-Named-Distinguished-Chapter-Officer-Teams 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-04-08T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Tuesday, April 8, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Jackson, MS - Thirty Phi Theta Kappa chapter officer teams will be honored with the 2014 Distinguished Chapter Officer Team Awards, presented by Phi Theta Kappa Honor Society during &lt;a href="http://nerdnation.ptk.org/"&gt;NerdNation 2014&lt;/a&gt;, the annual convention in Orlando, Florida, April 24-26. Recipients will receive commemorative medallions and be honored during the Hallmark Awards Gala.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Distinguished Chapter Officer Teams must be nominated by their chapter advisors through the &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/benefits/awards/hallmark"&gt;Hallmark Awards&lt;/a&gt; application process and are chosen based on the team&amp;rsquo;s demonstration of an exceptional atmosphere of teamwork, leadership abilities, promotion of Honors in Action, other engagement in the Society and enthusiasm for the Hallmarks of the Society (Scholarship, Leadership, Service and Fellowship). They were selected by a panel of judges from more than 200 nominees internationally.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;The 2014 Distinguished Chapter Officer Team Award winners are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Beta Upsilon Chapter, Redlands Community College, El Reno, Oklahoma&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Gamma Omega Chapter, Valencia College, Orlando, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Kappa Sigma Chapter, Red Rocks Community College, Lakewood, Colorado&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Lambda Alpha Chapter, Hillsborough Community College, Tampa, Florida&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Lambda Sigma Chapter, Holmes Community College, Ridgeland, Mississippi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Mu Tau Chapter, Collin College, Frisco, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Nu Xi Chapter, College of the Canyons, Santa Clarita, California&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Omicron Chapter, Tyler Junior College, Tyler, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Pi Sigma Chapter, Metropolitan Community College - Blue River, Independence, Missouri&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Rho Pi Chapter, Northwestern Michigan College, Traverse City, Michigan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Rho Tau Chapter, Ivy Tech Community College of Indiana, Franklin, Indiana&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Rho Xi Chapter, New Mexico State University, Carlsbad, New Mexico&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Sigma Phi Chapter, Clark College, Vancouver, Washington&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Theta Delta Chapter, Central Arizona College, Coolidge, Arizona&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Xi Pi Chapter, Motlow State Community College, Lynchburg, Tennessee&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Zeta Iota Chapter, Northwest Shoals Community College, Phil Campbell, Alabama&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alpha Zeta Omicron Chapter, Cedar Valley College, Lancaster, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Beta Alpha Delta Chapter, Central Community College, Hastings, Nebraska&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Beta Lambda Delta Chapter, Jefferson State Community College, Birmingham, Alabama&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Beta Lambda Kappa Chapter, Macomb Community College, Warren, Michigan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Chi Omega Chapter, Cuyahoga Community College, Parma, Ohio&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Eta Gamma Chapter, Coffeyville Community College, Coffeyville, Kansas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lambda Chapter, Mineral Area College, Flat River, Missouri&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Omega Omega Chapter, Mountain View College, Dallas, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Omega Sigma Chapter, Houston Community College, Houston, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Omicron Beta Chapter, Mesa Community College, Mesa, Arizona&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Omicron Psi Chapter, Grayson College, Denison, Texas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Phi Upsilon Chapter, Alabama Southern Community College, Monroeville, Alabama&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rho Sigma Chapter, Jones County Junior College, Ellisville, Mississippi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tau Theta Chapter, Labette Community College, Parsons, Kansas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Phi Theta Kappa Honor Society, headquartered in Jackson, Mississippi, is the largest honor society in higher education with 1,285 chapters on college campuses in all 50 of the United States, plus Canada, Germany, the Republic of Palau, Peru, the Republic of the Marshall Islands, the Federated States of Micronesia, the British Virgin Islands, the United Arab Emirates and U.S. territorial possessions. Nearly 3 million students have been inducted since its founding in 1918, with approximately 131,000 students inducted annually.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/191" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Events &amp;amp; Awards&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-item odd"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/192" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Press Room&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
