     <title>Engage in Phi Theta Kappa Programs through Ed Forums</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/engage-in-programs-through-ed-forums 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-03-25T00:00:00-05:00"&gt;Tuesday, March 25, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Educational Forums offer an opportunity for you to connect personally with Phi Theta Kappa Headquarters staff. The offerings at &lt;a href="http://nerdnation.ptk.org"&gt;NerdNation 2014&lt;/a&gt; cover a wide range of Society programming that can lead to success for your chapter and its members.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Topics exploring Honors in Action, CollegeFish.org and the fifth edition of Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Leadership Textbook will be offered, in addition to advisor-only sessions that will guide you through ways the Society can help you achieve your chapter&amp;#39;s goals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Participating in the Educational Forums is a must if you want the full NerdNation Experience,&amp;rdquo; said Jennifer Stanford, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Chief Student Engagement Officer. &amp;ldquo;With more than 3,500 people in the General Sessions, the Ed Forums are where you&amp;rsquo;ll be able to talk in a more intimate setting with the Headquarters staff, other expert presenters and, of course, like-minded Phi Theta Kappa members and advisors.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Approximately 75 forums will be presented during NerdNation 2014. Five rounds of Educational Forums will be held:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Round 1: Thursday, April 24, 1:30-2:30 p.m.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Round 2: Thursday, April 24, 3-4 p.m.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Round 3: Friday, April 25, 8:30-9:30 a.m.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Round 4: Saturday, April 26, 10-11 a.m.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Round 5: Saturday, April 26, 1:45-2:45 p.m.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The forums are led by Society staff members, chapter advisors and members, four-year college and student development professionals. Their skills are directly related to the forum discussions they are leading, so you know the information you are gaining is solid and sound.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Below is a sampling of Educational Forums exploring Society programs. A full schedule of offerings will be announced soon.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CollegeFish.org 101: How New Members Can Get Hooked on CollegeFish.org | Rounds 1, 2, 5 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;CollegeFish.org Minnows &amp;mdash; aka new members &amp;mdash; learn how Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s online college transfer tool can help you reel in scholarships and the four-year university of your dreams.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advisors Only: Work Smarter, Not Harder | Divisions I &amp;amp; III: Rounds 1, 4; Divisions II &amp;amp; IV: Rounds 3, 5 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Headquarters staff show you how to leverage Society tools to increase membership. Learn how the Membership Recruitment Campaign Administered by Headquarters and online membership acceptance can be smart solutions to getting more done in less time. Plus get a PAM tutorial, and together we&amp;rsquo;ll troubleshoot your biggest recruitment challenges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Honors in Action: Transform Your Chapter&amp;rsquo;s Approach to the Honors Study Topic | Rounds 1, 2, 3 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Discover effective ways to develop an Honors in Action project through Honors Study Topic research, leadership development, service learning and collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Edge: Your Ticket to Professionalism | Round 1 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Soft skills don&amp;rsquo;t have to be hard! Let our professional development plan for members and alumni help you strengthen communication, critical thinking and professional etiquette skills that will help you better compete for jobs, scholarships and transferring.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phi Theta Kappa Leadership Development Studies (Fifth Edition) | Rounds 2, 4 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Explore exciting changes to the fifth edition of Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Leadership Development Program text. Certified leadership instructors and those who want to be certified to teach the course are encouraged to attend.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hites Scholarship: Tips &amp;amp; Advice from Winning Scholars | Rounds 4, 5 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Learn winning strategies for writing Hites Scholarship applications.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2014 Honors Institute | Round 4 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Hear all about the 2014 Honors Institute, the &amp;ldquo;crown jewel&amp;rdquo; of Phi Theta Kappa programming, which will be held at Washington University in St. Louis.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Edge: From the Mouths of Members | Round 5 &amp;mdash; &lt;/strong&gt;Members share their first-hand experiences of becoming Five Star Members through Phi Theta Kappa&amp;#39;s professional development plan, which helps strengthen marketable skills.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/191" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Events &amp;amp; Awards&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
