    <item> 
     <title>Tips for a Successful Scholarship Application</title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/successful-scholarship-app-tips 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-02-25T00:00:00-06:00"&gt;Tuesday, February 25, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hundreds of Phi Theta Kappa members apply for scholarships using the Spring Common App each year. So how do you make sure your application has a competitive edge?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="caption_photo right"&gt;&lt;a class="colorbox colorbox-insert-image" href="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/ptk_scholarships.png" rel="gallery-all" title=""&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/ptk_scholarships.png?itok=mUbozzpD" title="" typeof="foaf:Image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Heather Johnson, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Director of Scholarship Programs, shares these tips that will help your scholarship application shine above the others!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply EARLY! &amp;bull; &lt;/strong&gt;Deadlines can make or break you. &amp;bull; Official transcripts can take time to obtain, and overnight mailing is EXPENSIVE. &amp;bull; Online applications cannot be completed two hours ahead of deadline; give yourself time, as you might run into technological or login problems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply OFTEN!&lt;/strong&gt; Practice hones your writing skills and makes everything better.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create a scholarship RESUME. &lt;/strong&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll want to include the following items:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Education&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Campus Involvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Community Service&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Scholarships and Awards&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work Experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read the PURPOSE of the Scholarship.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish solid LETTERS OF RECOMMENDATION.&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;bull; Choose someone who knows you well and can provide specific and pertinent information. &amp;bull; Explain the criteria of the award &amp;mdash; photocopy the application for them. &amp;bull; Give recommenders ample time to compose their letter for you. Send thank-you notes to them afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When writing your ESSAY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stick to the topic.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use vivid details. They&amp;rsquo;ll make your application stand out.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;PROOFREAD, PROOFREAD, PROOFREAD!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your application should be NEAT and EASY TO READ.&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;bull; Type everything (if paper) or proofread (if online). Never submit your first draft. &amp;bull; Organize information with bullets. &amp;bull; This is your one chance in front of the judges &amp;mdash; make a good impression!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have MULTIPLE persons CRITIQUE your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double-check your application for COMPLETION. &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;An incomplete application is as good as NO application.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHOTOCOPY or PRINT your application before submission. &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;bull; You can use it as a reference. &amp;bull; If it gets lost, you&amp;rsquo;ll have a spare.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Above all, do not miss the deadline! Applications are due April 30, 2014!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Read more about the scholarships offered on the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/news/spring-common-scholarship-app"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Spring Common Scholarship Application.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/190" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
     <pubdate>
      Fri, 21 Feb 2014 02:31:35 +0000
     </pubdate> 
     <dc:creator>
      cogsweep
     </dc:creator> 
     <guid ispermalink="false">
