    <item> 
     <title>Register Now for 2014 Honors Institute </title> 
     <link>https://www.ptk.org/news/honors-institute-registration-open 
     <description>
      &lt;div class="field field-name-field-dateline field-type-datestamp field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2014-02-18T00:00:00-06:00"&gt;Tuesday, February 18, 2014&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Registration is now open for the &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/honors/institute"&gt;2014 Honors Institute,&lt;/a&gt; to be held June 16-21 at Washington University in St. Louis, Missouri.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="caption_photo right"&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/brookings_hall.jpg" title="" class="colorbox colorbox-insert-image" rel="gallery-all"&gt;&lt;img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.ptk.org/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/brookings_hall.jpg?itok=U_cN_xRB" alt="" title="" class="" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;p&gt;The site of the 2014 Honors Institute, Washington University, St. Louis, Missouri&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;Honors Institute is a special experience that provides perhaps the best opportunity to learn what Phi Theta Kappa is really all about. There&amp;rsquo;s an intimacy to Honors Institute that, through a limited number of attendees and small seminar group discussions, fosters learning and friendship.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Honors Institute is all about student success,&amp;rdquo; said Susan Edwards, Phi Theta Kappa&amp;rsquo;s Dean of Academic Affairs and Honors Programs. &amp;ldquo;Our program affords members and advisors the opportunity to engage in interdisciplinary inquiry, raise their global awareness, and experience deep learning.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Register before May 16 using the &lt;a href="https://www.ptk.org/honors/institute/register"&gt;new online submission form&lt;/a&gt; to receive the lowest rate of $895 per person. Attendance is limited to approximately 500 people and is filled on a first-come, first-served basis. The registration fee covers lodging in a campus residence hall, dinner Monday evening, all meals on Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday, and breakfast on Saturday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Honors Institute is often called the &amp;ldquo;crown jewel&amp;rdquo; of honors programming. It is a special week of intense study of the &lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/get-involved/honors-in-action"&gt;2014/2015 Honors Study Topic, &lt;em&gt;Frontiers and the Spirit of Exploration,&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that can and often does directly impact the success of a chapter. Features of the event include internationally recognized speakers, small group seminars, educational field trips and experiential activities.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;It gives the students the opportunity to grow academically without the stress of a grade,&amp;rdquo; said Dr. Mary James, advisor of the Upsilon Eta Chapter from Florida State College at Jacksonville. &amp;ldquo;Since it is an open discussion format, it allows the students the chance to develop a technique to express themselves. I have seen some personal growth in students as well as in myself.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 2014 Honors Institute speakers are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class="default"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 1: Patrick Lee as Captain William Clark &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash; Lee is a professional speaker, actor and writer who has written a series of 21 articles about the Lewis and Clark Expedition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 2: Nina Tandon&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; Tandon is a tissue engineer and a Senior TED Fellow studying electrical signaling with the goal of creating &amp;ldquo;spare parts&amp;rdquo; &amp;mdash; artificial hearts and bones &amp;mdash; for human implantation and/or disease models.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 3: Dr. Ray Arvidson&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; Arvidson is head of NASA&amp;rsquo;s Planetary Data System Geosciences Node and is the James S. McDonnell Distinguished University Professor and Chair of the Department of Earth and Planetary Sciences at Washington University.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 5: Ken Ramirez&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; Ramirez develops and supervises animal care programs, staff training and development as well as public presentation programs for the entire animal collection at Chicago&amp;rsquo;s Shedd Aquarium.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 6: Dr. Sylvia Earle&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; Dubbed a &amp;ldquo;Hero for the Planet&amp;rdquo; by &lt;em&gt;Time&lt;/em&gt; magazine, Earle is an oceanographer, explorer, author, lecturer and Phi Theta Kappa alumna.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Session 7: Pokey LaFarge&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; LaFarge is a musician, songwriter, bandleader, entertainer, innovator and preservationist whose well-rounded arsenal of talents has placed him at the forefront of American music.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;General Session 4 will take attendees on a visit to the St. Louis Arch and Gateway Museum and the Old Courthouse, in addition to a riverboat ride along the Mississippi River.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thursday, June 19, is R&amp;amp;R Day, giving attendees the opportunity to explore St. Louis on their own. Participants are responsible for the cost of any meals, trips, tours and admission fees on R&amp;amp;R Day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ptk.org/honors/institute"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Get all of the 2014 Honors Institute details and register now!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field field-name-field-article-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix"&gt;&lt;div class="field-label"&gt;Tags:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="field-items"&gt;&lt;div class="field-item even"&gt;&lt;a href="/taxonomy/term/191" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype=""&gt;Events &amp;amp; Awards&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
     </description> 
     <pubdate>
      Fri, 14 Feb 2014 19:34:02 +0000
